Groepe was first appointed Deputy Governor of the SARB in January 2012 for a five year term ending on 31 December 2016.His involvement at the South African Reserve Bank dates back to July 2004 when he was appointed as a Non-Executive Director. Groepe is currently the Chairperson of both the South African Bank Note Company and the South African Mint Company, subsidiaries of the Reserve Bank that produce the country s currency as well as currencies of other countries.